17 SECTION 2.
18 The election superintendent of Toombs County shall call and conduct an election, as
19 provided in this section, for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of Toombs
20 County for approval or rejection. The election superintendent shall conduct that election on
21 the Tuesday after the first Monday in November, 2025, and shall issue the call and conduct
22 that election as provided by general law. The election superintendent shall cause the date and
23 purpose of the election to be published once at least 90 days immediately preceding the date
24 thereof and once a week for two weeks immediately preceding the date thereof in the official
25 organ of Toombs County. The ballot shall have written or printed thereon the words:
26 "( ) YES Shall the Act be approved which authorizes Toombs County to exercise all
27 ( ) NO redevelopment powers allowed under the 'Redevelopment Powers Law,' as
28 it may be amended from time to time?"
29 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
30 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
31 such question are for approval of the Act, then Section 1 of this Act shall become of full
32 force and effect immediately. If this Act is not so approved or if the election is not
33 conducted as provided in this section, Section 1 of this Act shall not become effective and
34 this Act shall be automatically repealed on the first day of January immediately following
35 such election date. The expense of such election shall be borne by Toombs County. It shall
36 be the election superintendent's duty to certify the result thereof to the Secretary of State.
37 SECTION 3.
38 Except as otherwise provided in Section 2 of this Act, this Act shall become effective upon
39 its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law without such approval.
40 SECTION 4.
41 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
